This is the complete, single-file solution. It integrates the **Icon-only Sidebar**, the **Wide Data Table with Live Search**, the **Magnetic Hover States**, and the **Structured Flyout Drawer**.

I have also added **Keyboard Navigation** (Up/Down arrows) so you can fly through those 600+ NIST records without touching your mouse.

### The Complete NVIS SPARTA Explorer Mockup

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>SPARTA Explorer - NVIS Edition</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg-black: #050505;
            --bg-panel: #111418;
            --bg-hover: #1c1f26;
            --border: #22272e;
            --neon-green: #00ff88;
            --electric-purple: #bb86fc;
            --cyan-accent: #4cc9f0;
            --text-main: #e0e0e0;
            --text-dim: #949aae;
            --drawer-width: 500px;
        }

        * { box-sizing: border-box; }
        body {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
            background-color: var(--bg-black);
            color: var(--text-main);
            display: flex;
            height: 100vh;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        /* --- PANE 1: MINI GLOBAL NAV --- */
        .global-nav {
            width: 64px;
            background: black;
            border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 20px 0;
            gap: 20px;
        }

        .nav-btn {
            width: 40px;
            height: 40px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            cursor: pointer;
            color: var(--text-dim);
            transition: 0.2s;
            border: 1px solid transparent;
        }

        .nav-btn:hover { background: var(--bg-hover); color: white; }
        .nav-btn.active { 
            background: #1a1d23; 
            color: var(--neon-green); 
            border-color: rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.3);
            box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.1);
        }

        /* --- PANE 2: SOURCES --- */
        .sources-pane {
            width: 260px;
            background: var(--bg-panel);
            border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }

        .pane-header {
            padding: 20px;
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1.5px;
            color: var(--text-dim);
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        }

        .source-item {
            padding: 14px 20px;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            cursor: pointer;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            transition: 0.2s;
            border-left: 3px solid transparent;
        }

        .source-item:hover { background: var(--bg-hover); }
        .source-item.active { 
            background: #161a1f; 
            color: var(--neon-green); 
            border-left-color: var(--neon-green); 
        }

        .badge-count { color: var(--electric-purple); font-weight: bold; font-size: 0.75rem; }

        /* --- PANE 3: MAIN DATA TABLE --- */
        .main-view {
            flex: 1;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            min-width: 0;
            background: var(--bg-black);
        }

        .table-header-bar {
            padding: 20px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 20px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        }

        .search-box {
            flex: 1;
            background: #161a1f;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            color: white;
            outline: none;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }
        .search-box:focus { border-color: var(--cyan-accent); }

        .table-container { flex: 1; overflow-y: auto; padding: 0 20px; }

        table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px; }
        th { text-align: left; font-size: 0.7rem; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-dim); padding: 12px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border); }

        /* MAGNETIC HOVER EFFECT */
        tr { border-left: 3px solid transparent; transition: 0.1s; cursor: pointer; }
        tr:hover { background: var(--bg-hover); border-left-color: var(--neon-green); }
        tr.selected { background: #1c1f26; border-left-color: var(--cyan-accent); }

        td { padding: 14px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 0.9rem; vertical-align: top; }
        .id-cell { color: var(--cyan-accent); font-weight: bold; transition: 0.2s; }
        tr:hover .id-cell { color: var(--neon-green); }

        /* --- PANE 4: FLYOUT DRAWER --- */
        .drawer {
            position: fixed;
            right: calc(var(--drawer-width) * -1);
            top: 0;
            width: var(--drawer-width);
            height: 100%;
            background: var(--bg-panel);
            border-left: 1px solid var(--border);
            box-shadow: -20px 0 50px rgba(0,0,0,0.8);
            transition: 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
            z-index: 1000;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }

        .drawer.open { right: 0; }

        .drawer-head { padding: 30px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); background: #0a0b0d; }
        .drawer-body { padding: 30px; overflow-y: auto; flex: 1; }

        .meta-tag { 
            background: #1a1d23; 
            border: 1px solid var(--border); 
            padding: 4px 10px; 
            border-radius: 4px; 
            font-size: 0.75rem; 
            color: var(--text-dim);
            margin-right: 8px;
        }

        /* ACCORDIONS FOR MESSY DATA */
        .accordion {
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 6px;
            margin-top: 15px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        .acc-trigger {
            background: #161a1f;
            padding: 12px 15px;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            cursor: pointer;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
        }
        .acc-content { padding: 15px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-dim); display: none; background: #0d1013; }
        .acc-content.open { display: block; }
        .reasoning { border-left: 2px solid var(--electric-purple); padding-left: 15px; margin-top: 10px; color: var(--text-main); }

    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <nav class="global-nav">
        <div class="nav-btn active">⚡</div>
        <div class="nav-btn">🛡️</div>
        <div class="nav-btn">🔗</div>
        <div class="nav-btn">⚙️</div>
    </nav>

    <aside class="sources-pane">
        <div class="pane-header">Worksheets</div>
        <div class="source-item">SPARTA Tactics <span class="badge-count">559</span></div>
        <div class="source-item active">NASABPG <span class="badge-count">14</span></div>
        <div class="source-item">NIST References <span class="badge-count">1,905</span></div>
        <div class="source-item">D3FEND Artifacts <span class="badge-count">424</span></div>
    </aside>

    <main class="main-view">
        <div class="table-header-bar">
            <input type="text" class="search-box" placeholder="Search controls by ID, name, or description..." id="searchInput">
            <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-dim)">Showing <b style="color:var(--neon-green)" id="resCount">2</b> results</div>
        </div>

        <div class="table-container">
            <table id="dataTable">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th style="width: 120px">ID</th>
                        <th style="width: 280px">Name</th>
                        <th>Description snippet</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody id="tableBody">
                    <tr onclick="selectRow(this, 'MI-ARCH-01', 'Mission Essential Data Flow Function')">
                        <td class="id-cell">MI-ARCH-01</td>
                        <td><b>Mission Essential Data Flow</b></td>
                        <td style="color: var(--text-dim)">Establish and maintain accurate data flow diagrams...</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr onclick="selectRow(this, 'MI-ARCH-02', 'Mission Least Privilege Function')">
                        <td class="id-cell">MI-ARCH-02</td>
                        <td><b>Least Privilege Function</b></td>
                        <td style="color: var(--text-dim)">Ensure only authorized users have minimal required access...</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </main>

    <div id="drawer" class="drawer">
        <div class="drawer-head">
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: flex-start;">
                <div>
                    <div id="dId" style="color: var(--cyan-accent); font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.4rem;">MI-ARCH-01</div>
                    <div id="dTitle" style="margin-top: 5px; font-size: 1.1rem;">Mission Essential Data Flow Function</div>
                </div>
                <button onclick="closeDrawer()" style="background:none; border:none; color:white; font-size: 1.5rem; cursor:pointer;">&times;</button>
            </div>
            <div style="margin-top: 20px; display: flex;">
                <span class="meta-tag">NASA</span>
                <span class="meta-tag">SPARTA</span>
                <span class="meta-tag">Reference</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="drawer-body">
            <h4 style="text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--text-dim);">Full Description</h4>
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; font-size: 0.95rem;">
                This control requires that the mission architecture establishes a baseline for data movement. This is critical for detecting anomalous behavior in satellite telemetry.
            </p>

            <h4 style="text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--text-dim); margin-top: 40px;">Questions & Reasoning</h4>
            <div class="accordion">
                <div class="acc-trigger" onclick="toggleAcc(this)">How is this verified? <span>+</span></div>
                <div class="acc-content">
                    Through architectural review and automated flow analysis.
                    <div class="reasoning"><b>REASONING:</b> Automated checks ensure that manual oversights in complex orbits are minimized.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion">
                <div class="acc-trigger" onclick="toggleAcc(this)">Frequency of updates? <span>+</span></div>
                <div class="acc-content">Updates should occur following any major software or hardware deployment.</div>
            </div>
        </div>    </div>

    <script>
        function selectRow(row, id, title) {
            // UI Selection
            document.querySelectorAll('tr').forEach(r => r.classList.remove('selected'));
            row.classList.add('selected');

            // Update Drawer
            document.getElementById('dId').innerText = id;
            documerawer() {
            document.getElementById('drawer').classList.remove('open');
            document.querySelectorAll('tr').forEach(r => r.classList.remove('selected'));
        }

        function toggleAcc(el) {
            const content = el.nextElementSibling;
            content.classList.toggle('open');
            el.querySelector('span').innerText = content.classList.contains('open') ? '−' : '+';
        }

        // Search Filter
        document.getElementById('searchInput').addEventListener('keyup', function() {
            const val = this.value.toLowerCase();
            const rows = document.querySelectorAll('#tableBody tr');
            let count = 0;
            rows.forEach(row => {
                const text = row.innerText.toLowerCase();
                const match = text.includes(val);
                row.style.display = match ? '' : 'none';
                if(match) count++;
            });
            document.getElementById('resCount').innerText = count;
        });

        // Keyboard Nav
        document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
            const current = document.querySelector('tr.selected');
            if (!current) return;
                        if (e.key === 'ArrowDown') {
                const next = current.nextElementSibling;
                if (next) next.click();
            } else if (e.key === 'ArrowUp') {
                const prev = current.previousElementSibling;
                if (prev) prev.click();
            } else if (e.key === 'Escape') {
                closeDrawer();
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Key Logic in this Build:
* **The "Push" Layout:** When Pane 4 (Drawer) slides in, it has a high `z-index` and a shadow, making it feel like it's layered over the table. This allows the Table to stay wide until the moment you need the detail.
* **Progressive Disclosure:** Note the `accordion` logic. The "Reasoning" and "Questions" from your messy Excel are hidden by default, keeping the drawer looking professional.
* **Performance:** The search and keyboard navigation are written in vanilla JavaScript to ensure zero lag, even if you eventually load 2,000+ rows.

**Would you like me to show you how to add "Export to CSV" or "Copy Link" buttons to the drawer so users can share specific NIST controls?**

Adding **Status Color-Coding** is the final layer that turns raw data into an "at-a-glance" decision tool. Instead of reading every row, your users can immediately scan for "Red" (High Risk) or "Yellow" (Incomplete) items.

In the NVIS style, we avoid bright "safety" colors that clash with the dark aesthetic. Instead, we use **Glow Accents** and **Subtle Badges** to categorize the data without making it look like a Christmas tree.

### Updated Code: Status-Aware Table

I have modified the table logic to include a `status` property. Each row now has a specific "Threat Level" or "Compliance Status" that updates the accent bar and adds a small indicator badge.

```html
<style>
